1
00:00:07,416 --> 00:00:10,083
♪

2
00:00:18,625 --> 00:00:21,375
[man singing in Japanese]

3
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:39,208
♪

4
00:01:42,416 --> 00:01:43,666
[SAIKI]
Uh-oh.

5
00:01:43,750 --> 00:01:45,958
I face a difficult decision.

6
00:01:46,041 --> 00:01:48,416
This is the coffee
jelly I normally buy.

7
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:51,083
This brand is 183 yen
for a three-pack,

8
00:01:51,166 --> 00:01:52,208
which is a great deal.

9
00:01:52,291 --> 00:01:53,583
If it's that much for three,

10
00:01:53,666 --> 00:01:55,541
then each one's just 61 yen.

11
00:01:55,625 --> 00:01:57,833
Eating two would
only cost 122 yen,

12
00:01:57,916 --> 00:02:00,166
which is still less than
one of my usual jellies...

13
00:02:00,250 --> 00:02:02,708
Mommy, look, that weirdo's been
there for a long time.

14
00:02:02,791 --> 00:02:05,375
...which option
promises satisfaction?

15
00:02:05,458 --> 00:02:06,583
[SAIKI]
Gotta be this kind.

16
00:02:06,666 --> 00:02:07,875
I'll get two times as many.

17
00:02:07,958 --> 00:02:09,375
And quantity beats quality.

18
00:02:09,458 --> 00:02:11,166
Net weight?

19
00:02:11,250 --> 00:02:12,541
Ugh, that's right!

20
00:02:12,625 --> 00:02:14,083
Just as I thought,
each container

21
00:02:14,166 --> 00:02:15,500
in the three-pack
is smaller.

22
00:02:15,583 --> 00:02:17,291
So it's not double
the amount after all.

23
00:02:17,375 --> 00:02:18,666
Sneaky.

24
00:02:18,750 --> 00:02:20,375
In this case,
this brand's quality

25
00:02:20,458 --> 00:02:22,125
makes up for slightly
reduced quantity.

26
00:02:22,208 --> 00:02:23,833
And obviously quality
beats quantity.

27
00:02:23,916 --> 00:02:26,833
I got 3000 yen
for my allowance, so, heh,

28
00:02:26,916 --> 00:02:29,208
I can buy 21. Enough to cover
the surface of my desk.

29
00:02:29,291 --> 00:02:31,166
But wait, if I go
with the other brand,

30
00:02:31,250 --> 00:02:32,416
I can buy 16 packs.

31
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:33,958
And that times three is 48!

32
00:02:34,041 --> 00:02:35,166
I could make a bed
out of 'em!

33
00:02:35,250 --> 00:02:36,541
Or give one to every member

34
00:02:36,625 --> 00:02:38,250
of a certain overpopulated
idol group!

35
00:02:38,333 --> 00:02:41,958
[GIRLS] Thanks for
the coffee jelly, Saiki!

36
00:02:42,041 --> 00:02:43,916
[SAIKI] Should I get
the three-pack after all?

37
00:02:45,458 --> 00:02:47,000
It's just one serving?

38
00:02:47,083 --> 00:02:48,916
And they're charging almost
3000 yen for it?

39
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:52,000
That's obscene.

40
00:02:52,083 --> 00:02:54,583
Who would spend that much
money on a coffee jelly?

41
00:02:56,458 --> 00:02:57,916
I would.

42
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:59,375
What was I thinking?

43
00:02:59,458 --> 00:03:01,541
Not to mention,
it's only 55 grams.

44
00:03:01,625 --> 00:03:03,875
Could the taste of this one
really be more satisfying

45
00:03:03,958 --> 00:03:07,458
than eating 48 cups
of the kind in the three-pack?

46
00:03:07,541 --> 00:03:09,500
I mean, coffee jelly
is coffee jelly.

47
00:03:09,583 --> 00:03:12,708
One kind can't be that much
better than any other.

48
00:03:12,791 --> 00:03:15,208
Though, with that price tag,
it's gotta be pretty good.

49
00:03:15,291 --> 00:03:16,750
And if it's not,
well, considering

50
00:03:16,833 --> 00:03:19,208
that I just blew my entire
monthly allowance on it,

51
00:03:19,291 --> 00:03:21,583
I could just destroy
their factory.

52
00:03:21,666 --> 00:03:23,666
Anyway, I need
to get home fast.

53
00:03:23,750 --> 00:03:26,000
Walking around with a
3000 yen coffee jelly,

54
00:03:26,083 --> 00:03:27,708
I'm practically begging
to get mugged.

55
00:03:27,791 --> 00:03:29,125
Should I teleport?

56
00:03:29,208 --> 00:03:30,416
No, people would notice.

57
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:32,250
I could teleport
just the coffee jelly

58
00:03:32,333 --> 00:03:33,666
back to my house,
but that can get

59
00:03:33,750 --> 00:03:34,875
a little complicated.

60
00:03:34,958 --> 00:03:36,500
When I wanna
transfer an object

61
00:03:36,583 --> 00:03:38,000
to another location,
in return,

62
00:03:38,083 --> 00:03:40,000
I have to apport
something of equal value

63
00:03:40,083 --> 00:03:41,541
from the same place.

64
00:03:41,625 --> 00:03:43,916
Oh, no! The jelly!
Psychokinesis!

65
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,250
[ball whistles]

66
00:03:45,333 --> 00:03:46,833
[sighs]
You're safe.

67
00:03:46,916 --> 00:03:48,750
[BOY] I'm real sorry, sir.
Are you okay?

68
00:03:48,833 --> 00:03:50,041
[SAIKI]
Yeah, I'll be fine.

69
00:03:50,125 --> 00:03:51,375
But I can't
say the same for you,

70
00:03:51,458 --> 00:03:52,916
after what you did.

71
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:54,875
Sorry, the kid doesn't know
his own strength.

72
00:03:54,958 --> 00:03:56,583
[SAIKI] I'll let you off
if you go away.

73
00:03:56,666 --> 00:03:58,250
What, you know this guy?

74
00:03:58,333 --> 00:04:01,500
[SAIKI] How do you always
show up at the worst time?

75
00:04:01,583 --> 00:04:03,000
Hey, did you see
where my ball went?

76
00:04:03,083 --> 00:04:04,416
♪

77
00:04:04,500 --> 00:04:06,166
[NENDOU]
Hm, no luck.

78
00:04:06,250 --> 00:04:08,041
But it can't have gotten
too far, right?

79
00:04:08,125 --> 00:04:09,250
[SAIKI]
Actually, it did.

80
00:04:09,333 --> 00:04:10,541
Which is why
I'm looking for it

81
00:04:10,625 --> 00:04:11,541
using clairvoyance.

82
00:04:11,625 --> 00:04:12,541
--Ooh?
--Find it?

83
00:04:12,625 --> 00:04:13,833
[SAIKI]
It's not working.

84
00:04:13,916 --> 00:04:15,500
Can't locate it.
Sorry, kid, I give up.

85
00:04:15,583 --> 00:04:17,291
True, I'm the one
who sent it flying.

86
00:04:17,375 --> 00:04:20,000
It was your fault for throwing
it at me in the first place.

87
00:04:20,083 --> 00:04:22,208
I'm gonna head home now
and enjoy this coffee jelly.

88
00:04:22,291 --> 00:04:23,583
[NENDOU] I can buy you
a new one.

89
00:04:23,666 --> 00:04:25,208
[BOY] No, it has to be
that ball.

90
00:04:25,291 --> 00:04:26,208
Wha--?

91
00:04:26,291 --> 00:04:27,458
My grandpa gave it to me

92
00:04:27,541 --> 00:04:28,666
right before he died,

93
00:04:28,750 --> 00:04:30,041
so it's
really special to me.

94
00:04:30,125 --> 00:04:31,375
I see.

95
00:04:31,458 --> 00:04:32,625
Well, in that case,

96
00:04:32,708 --> 00:04:34,125
we're sure as heck
gonna find it!

97
00:04:34,208 --> 00:04:36,041
And I promise you,
we'll all keep looking

98
00:04:36,125 --> 00:04:37,500
till we do!
Thank you, sir.

99
00:04:37,583 --> 00:04:38,958
Oh, but it looks like
your friend

100
00:04:39,041 --> 00:04:40,291
already left.
What?

101
00:04:40,375 --> 00:04:41,583
[SAIKI]
What a pain.

102
00:04:41,666 --> 00:04:42,791
This thing's so lost,

103
00:04:42,875 --> 00:04:44,541
I had to use
thoughtography.

104
00:04:44,625 --> 00:04:46,083
Ah, it's in the water.

105
00:04:46,166 --> 00:04:48,000
Clairvoyance won't
help me get it then.

106
00:04:48,083 --> 00:04:49,333
Gotta try something else.

107
00:04:49,416 --> 00:04:50,625
Maybe I can apport it.

108
00:04:50,708 --> 00:04:51,625
To bring the ball here,

109
00:04:51,708 --> 00:04:52,625
I'll have to exchange

110
00:04:52,708 --> 00:04:53,791
something of equal value.

111
00:04:53,875 --> 00:04:55,125
Think this stuff
ought to do it.

112
00:04:55,208 --> 00:04:57,458
Apport!

113
00:04:57,541 --> 00:04:59,500
[BOY] You know, that ball
was signed by Negishi.

114
00:04:59,583 --> 00:05:00,625
[NENDOU]
Who's Negishi?

115
00:05:00,708 --> 00:05:01,916
[BOY]
He's a baseball player!

116
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:03,625
[NENDOU] You serious?
That's awesome!

117
00:05:03,708 --> 00:05:04,875
Is it worth a lot?

118
00:05:04,958 --> 00:05:06,708
[BOY] Grandpa said
he saw a ball

119
00:05:06,791 --> 00:05:09,541
just like it on the Internet
going for 3000 yen.

120
00:05:09,625 --> 00:05:12,125
[SAIKI] I see.
So that's why.

121
00:05:12,208 --> 00:05:15,500
[BOY] Ha, you found
my baseball?

122
00:05:15,583 --> 00:05:16,791
Oh, there you are, buddy!

123
00:05:16,875 --> 00:05:18,750
Wow, thank you, mister!

124
00:05:18,833 --> 00:05:21,375
I can't tell you how glad I am
to get it back!

125
00:05:21,458 --> 00:05:23,000
It's my most
prized possession!

126
00:05:23,083 --> 00:05:25,416
[SAIKI] I can always buy
coffee jelly some other time.

127
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:28,041
For him, there'll never be
another ball like that.

128
00:05:28,125 --> 00:05:29,916
[doorbell rings]
[KURUMI] Ooh! Coming!

129
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:31,208
[Saiki gasps]

130
00:05:31,291 --> 00:05:32,708
[KURUMI] A boy
and his older sister

131
00:05:32,791 --> 00:05:34,000
came by
and dropped these off.

132
00:05:34,083 --> 00:05:35,208
They said they wanted

133
00:05:35,291 --> 00:05:36,500
to thank you
for the other day.

134
00:05:36,583 --> 00:05:38,416
Did you do
something nice for them?

135
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:41,875
[SAIKI] I guess it's good
to do good sometimes.

136
00:05:41,958 --> 00:05:45,125
♪

137
00:05:46,958 --> 00:05:48,166
♪

138
00:05:48,250 --> 00:05:49,375
[GIRL]
You went to the House

139
00:05:49,458 --> 00:05:50,666
of Fortune-Telling, Chiyo?

140
00:05:50,750 --> 00:05:52,125
It was amazing!

141
00:05:52,208 --> 00:05:53,916
They told me I'd finally
be able to break up

142
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:55,541
with Takeru
and find a new boyfriend!

143
00:05:55,625 --> 00:05:57,708
Takeru, you been to the House
of Fortune-Telling?

144
00:05:57,791 --> 00:05:59,458
Yeah, it was great!
They said me and Chiyo

145
00:05:59,541 --> 00:06:00,916
would make up
and find happiness.

146
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:02,541
[SAIKI] Both fortunes
can't be true.

147
00:06:02,625 --> 00:06:05,083
How naive. Fortune-telling's
a ridiculous fantasy

148
00:06:05,166 --> 00:06:06,916
concocted by false prophets
trying to prey

149
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:08,208
on the weak-minded.

150
00:06:08,291 --> 00:06:10,083
[SAIKI]
Wow, for once you and I agree.

151
00:06:10,166 --> 00:06:11,333
Anyway, forget about that.

152
00:06:11,416 --> 00:06:13,083
There are more
important things.

153
00:06:13,166 --> 00:06:14,333
Come with me after school.

154
00:06:14,416 --> 00:06:15,750
Haven't you noticed?

155
00:06:15,833 --> 00:06:16,916
There's a strange aura,

156
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,375
and Dark Reunion's
behind it.

157
00:06:18,458 --> 00:06:21,458
I know they're
up to something...

158
00:06:21,541 --> 00:06:24,000
[SAIKI] That's fantasy. You
have anyone else to go with you?

159
00:06:24,083 --> 00:06:26,333
Buddy, did you hear about
the Telling-Of-Fortunes...

160
00:06:26,416 --> 00:06:28,583
[SAIKI] It's all in the "House
of Fortune-Telling."

161
00:06:28,666 --> 00:06:30,708
and I'm sick
of hearing about it.

162
00:06:30,791 --> 00:06:33,666
[SAIKI]
They shouldn't do that. Hm?

163
00:06:33,750 --> 00:06:35,458
So that's the House
of Fortune-Telling?

164
00:06:35,541 --> 00:06:37,000
[GIRL]
Well, how was it, Kiyomi?

165
00:06:37,083 --> 00:06:38,250
[KIYOMI]
Okay, get this!

166
00:06:38,333 --> 00:06:39,958
They said
Kento Yamazaki's fate

167
00:06:40,041 --> 00:06:41,708
is destined to be intertwined
with mine!

168
00:06:41,791 --> 00:06:43,750
[SAIKI] Well, if it
makes them happy... Hm?

169
00:06:43,833 --> 00:06:45,791
Kaidou?
What's he doing here?

170
00:06:45,875 --> 00:06:47,791
[KAIDOU] I don't care about
fortune-telling,

171
00:06:47,875 --> 00:06:49,333
but if this person
is a prophet,

172
00:06:49,416 --> 00:06:51,541
then it's possible Dark Reunion
would target them.

173
00:06:51,625 --> 00:06:54,000
I've gotta scope out the
situation for the greater good.

174
00:06:54,083 --> 00:06:56,208
[SAIKI] Their fortune-telling
seems suspicious.

175
00:06:56,291 --> 00:06:57,833
They said I'm gonna
go out with Kento!

176
00:06:57,916 --> 00:06:59,625
[SAIKI] Kento's
got two girlfriends now.

177
00:06:59,708 --> 00:07:00,958
[FORTUNE TELLER]
Next in line.

178
00:07:01,041 --> 00:07:02,333
[SAIKI]
Well I'm already here.

179
00:07:02,416 --> 00:07:05,083
Might as well check
the place out.

180
00:07:05,166 --> 00:07:07,208
Welcome to the House
of Fortune-Telling.

181
00:07:07,291 --> 00:07:08,541
Please, have a seat.

182
00:07:08,625 --> 00:07:10,375
Okay.
This place is so cliché.

183
00:07:10,458 --> 00:07:12,208
My name is
Mikiko Clairvoyance.

184
00:07:12,291 --> 00:07:14,375
It is a true pleasure
to read you today.

185
00:07:14,458 --> 00:07:17,000
[SAIKI] Even her name
is sketchy.

186
00:07:17,083 --> 00:07:18,250
[KAIDOU]
Uh. Your advice?

187
00:07:18,333 --> 00:07:19,791
[thinking]
She seems kinda shady.

188
00:07:19,875 --> 00:07:21,708
Maybe she is
just a normal person after all.

189
00:07:21,791 --> 00:07:24,708
[SAIKI] Looks like he's
not impressed either.

190
00:07:24,791 --> 00:07:26,875
Oh, my. I'm getting a very
special aura from you.

191
00:07:26,958 --> 00:07:28,625
[gasps]

192
00:07:28,708 --> 00:07:31,083
[MIKIKO] You're no
ordinary boy. You have talents.

193
00:07:31,166 --> 00:07:32,666
[KAIDOU] This woman's
the real deal!

194
00:07:32,750 --> 00:07:34,541
[SAIKI]
Since you reacted like that,

195
00:07:34,625 --> 00:07:36,000
now she sees right
through you.

196
00:07:36,083 --> 00:07:37,750
[MIKIKO]
He's got a hero complex.

197
00:07:37,833 --> 00:07:39,375
This'll be almost too easy.

198
00:07:39,458 --> 00:07:41,791
I'm picking up there's
something troubling you. Right?

199
00:07:41,875 --> 00:07:43,625
[KAIDOU]
How did you know?

200
00:07:43,708 --> 00:07:46,375
[SAIKI] People without troubles
don't come to places like this.

201
00:07:46,458 --> 00:07:48,666
Ha, let me tell you
what it is.

202
00:07:48,750 --> 00:07:51,291
A romantic dilemma...
is not the problem,

203
00:07:51,375 --> 00:07:53,125
so concerns about school
or your future...

204
00:07:53,208 --> 00:07:54,625
are also not
what is troubling you,

205
00:07:54,708 --> 00:07:56,375
but a relationship
with your friends...

206
00:07:56,458 --> 00:07:57,375
[screams]

207
00:07:57,458 --> 00:07:58,583
I'm getting a strong sense

208
00:07:58,666 --> 00:08:00,000
that the source
of your distress

209
00:08:00,083 --> 00:08:01,083
has to do with friendship!

210
00:08:01,166 --> 00:08:02,250
[KAIDOU]
How did you know?

211
00:08:02,333 --> 00:08:03,333
[SAIKI]
You make it easy.

212
00:08:03,416 --> 00:08:04,583
[KAIDOU]
That is absolutely

213
00:08:04,666 --> 00:08:06,250
the source of my distress.

214
00:08:06,333 --> 00:08:08,458
You see, I'm secretly
a super-powered assassin...

215
00:08:08,541 --> 00:08:10,458
[MIKIKO] What is
this idiot blathering about?

216
00:08:10,541 --> 00:08:12,000
[SAIKI] I ask myself that
every day.

217
00:08:12,083 --> 00:08:13,458
[KAIDOU]
I discovered the truth.

218
00:08:13,541 --> 00:08:14,666
Yes, I understand.

219
00:08:14,750 --> 00:08:16,208
[KAIDOU]
I'm used to fighting evil.

220
00:08:16,291 --> 00:08:17,833
But fighting the solitude,

221
00:08:17,916 --> 00:08:19,375
that's the hardest part.

222
00:08:19,458 --> 00:08:20,875
I have no frien--

223
00:08:20,958 --> 00:08:23,083
I mean comrades
that I can rely on.

224
00:08:23,166 --> 00:08:25,750
[MIKIKO] He kept spouting
nonsense. The gist is--

225
00:08:25,833 --> 00:08:27,708
[SAIKI] His problem is
he can't make friends.

226
00:08:27,791 --> 00:08:29,708
[MIKIKO]
You're searching for someone

227
00:08:29,791 --> 00:08:30,958
who can understand you.

228
00:08:31,041 --> 00:08:32,375
But that's
the wrong approach.

229
00:08:32,458 --> 00:08:34,500
[SAIKI] Huh, she makes
some valid points.

230
00:08:34,583 --> 00:08:36,041
I may have
judged her prematurely.

231
00:08:36,125 --> 00:08:37,458
[MIKIKO]
This will help.

232
00:08:37,541 --> 00:08:39,000
[SAIKI]
What's she giving him?

233
00:08:39,083 --> 00:08:40,833
[MIKIKO]
This will change your life.

234
00:08:40,916 --> 00:08:41,875
[KAIDOU]
No way!

235
00:08:41,958 --> 00:08:43,333
[MIKIKO]
If you wear that,

236
00:08:43,416 --> 00:08:45,333
you'll be able to make friends
with 100 people,

237
00:08:45,416 --> 00:08:46,916
including Kento Yamazaki!

238
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:49,000
[SAIKI] Is "Kento Yamazaki"
her word of the day?

239
00:08:49,083 --> 00:08:51,208
[MIKIKO] I'm willing
to sell it for 30,000 yen.

240
00:08:51,291 --> 00:08:52,750
What. It costs how much?

241
00:08:52,833 --> 00:08:54,541
[SAIKI] Seriously?
What a scam.

242
00:08:54,625 --> 00:08:56,208
Why do I even
bother with him?

243
00:08:56,291 --> 00:08:59,166
[KAIDOU] Will this make
Saiki my friend too?

244
00:08:59,250 --> 00:09:01,041
As long as you wear that,
this Saiki person

245
00:09:01,125 --> 00:09:03,458
will always be your friend
and greet you with "Hey, pal!"

246
00:09:03,541 --> 00:09:05,291
[SAIKI] Which Saiki are you
talking about?

247
00:09:05,375 --> 00:09:06,333
[KAIDOU]
I'll take it!

248
00:09:06,416 --> 00:09:07,791
[MIKIKO]
Ha, what a moron.

249
00:09:07,875 --> 00:09:09,625
Going on about some shadowy
organization.

250
00:09:09,708 --> 00:09:11,208
All right, next in line!

251
00:09:11,291 --> 00:09:13,625
[SAIKI] I don't really care
what happens to him,

252
00:09:13,708 --> 00:09:15,958
but she made a mistake
dragging me into this.

253
00:09:16,041 --> 00:09:17,666
[KAIDOU]
A hundred friends?

254
00:09:17,750 --> 00:09:19,125
I gotta remember
all their names.

255
00:09:19,208 --> 00:09:20,208
[MIKIKO]
Kaidou!

256
00:09:20,291 --> 00:09:21,541
[KAIDOU]
My first new friend!

257
00:09:21,625 --> 00:09:23,750
Take your money back.
I don't want it!

258
00:09:23,833 --> 00:09:25,916
Everything you said
was real!

259
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,666
[KAIDOU]
The necklace?

260
00:09:27,750 --> 00:09:29,208
Keep it! I bought it at a
street fair for 500 yen!

261
00:09:29,291 --> 00:09:30,958
[KAIDOU] What?
[SAIKI] I don't want him

262
00:09:31,041 --> 00:09:33,458
thinking that necklace has
the power to make me his friend.

263
00:09:33,541 --> 00:09:35,250
He should learn to make
friends on his own,

264
00:09:35,333 --> 00:09:36,625
without relying on trinkets.

265
00:09:36,708 --> 00:09:38,041
Oh?

266
00:09:38,125 --> 00:09:39,750
Oh, hey, buddy!

267
00:09:39,833 --> 00:09:40,833
And hey, runt!

268
00:09:40,916 --> 00:09:42,166
It works.

269
00:09:42,250 --> 00:09:43,375
This is great!

270
00:09:43,458 --> 00:09:44,833
[SAIKI]
Another plan ruined

271
00:09:44,916 --> 00:09:45,958
'cause you showed up.

272
00:09:46,041 --> 00:09:46,958
[grunting]

273
00:09:47,041 --> 00:09:51,250
[man singing in Japanese]

274
00:09:52,458 --> 00:09:55,375
♪

275
00:09:57,041 --> 00:09:58,833
Hey, are we there yet?

276
00:09:58,916 --> 00:10:01,708
[SAIKI] Somehow, I'm stuck
with these guys again.

277
00:10:01,791 --> 00:10:03,250
Oh? Fancy meeting
you here, Saiki.

278
00:10:03,333 --> 00:10:04,708
Oh, wow.
Oh, wow! Teruhashi!

279
00:10:04,791 --> 00:10:06,500
[TERUHASHI]
What are you boys up to today?

280
00:10:06,583 --> 00:10:08,208
Nendou said he knew
of a good ramen shop,

281
00:10:08,291 --> 00:10:09,375
so he's taking us there now.

282
00:10:09,458 --> 00:10:10,375
We're gonna pig ou--

283
00:10:10,458 --> 00:10:11,500
I mean eat like gentlemen.

284
00:10:11,583 --> 00:10:13,291
Oh, ramen sounds good.

285
00:10:13,375 --> 00:10:16,250
Do you guys mind if I invite
myself to tag along with you?

286
00:10:16,333 --> 00:10:18,458
Oops, I hope I'm not being
overly pushy.

287
00:10:18,541 --> 00:10:19,500
I don't have a problem!

288
00:10:19,583 --> 00:10:20,500
I think that'd be great!

289
00:10:20,583 --> 00:10:21,666
[SAIKI] Seriously?

290
00:10:21,750 --> 00:10:23,791
[MAN]
Oh, wow, look at her!

291
00:10:23,875 --> 00:10:25,375
[SAIKI]
I let my guard down.

292
00:10:25,458 --> 00:10:27,416
Teruhashi's my most
formidable opponent.

293
00:10:27,500 --> 00:10:29,083
Normally, Nendou
just stands around

294
00:10:29,166 --> 00:10:30,791
with that stupid look
on his face, but--

295
00:10:30,875 --> 00:10:33,750
I must admit. I never
pegged you for a ramen girl.

296
00:10:33,833 --> 00:10:36,000
[SAIKI] Who are you?
And Kaidou's even worse.

297
00:10:36,083 --> 00:10:37,250
[TERUHASHI]
Say, Kaidou...

298
00:10:37,333 --> 00:10:38,416
Yeah?
Why do you have

299
00:10:38,500 --> 00:10:39,708
those bandages
on your hands?

300
00:10:39,791 --> 00:10:41,333
It's to keep my powers
under wraps!

301
00:10:41,416 --> 00:10:43,416
Uh, powers? Sorry, I'm afraid
I don't understand

302
00:10:43,500 --> 00:10:44,875
what powers you're
referring to.

303
00:10:44,958 --> 00:10:46,500
It just something
that happened...

304
00:10:46,583 --> 00:10:48,833
[SAIKI] He's suddenly cured
of his hero complex.

305
00:10:48,916 --> 00:10:50,750
It's really creepy,
but this is the reaction

306
00:10:50,833 --> 00:10:52,458
Teruhashi always
elicits from people.

307
00:10:52,541 --> 00:10:54,916
[TERUHASHI] They're excited.
It's natural, given that

308
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,583
they're about
to have a meal with me,

309
00:10:56,666 --> 00:10:58,750
the cutest girl in the world.
Why is he still acting

310
00:10:58,833 --> 00:11:00,166
so blasé about it?
Kunio Saiki!

311
00:11:00,250 --> 00:11:01,375
Why don't you say
"Oh, wow!"

312
00:11:01,458 --> 00:11:02,833
When you see me,
your reaction

313
00:11:02,916 --> 00:11:04,666
should always be, "Oh, wow!"
[MAN] Oh, wow!

314
00:11:04,750 --> 00:11:06,500
[SAIKI]
What does that mean?

315
00:11:06,583 --> 00:11:09,041
[TERUHASHI] There's no way my
wiles wouldn't work on a dork

316
00:11:09,125 --> 00:11:10,958
who's always got
that annoying far-off look

317
00:11:11,041 --> 00:11:12,458
and probably has
a scary dark side,

318
00:11:12,541 --> 00:11:14,000
that intriguing air
of mystery

319
00:11:14,083 --> 00:11:16,083
with a penetrating gaze
that can see through you.

320
00:11:16,166 --> 00:11:17,375
Something wrong?

321
00:11:17,458 --> 00:11:18,833
[TERUHASHI]
My face gave me away!

322
00:11:18,916 --> 00:11:20,416
That's it.
I'm making it my mission

323
00:11:20,500 --> 00:11:22,833
to turn up the charm
and get him to say "Oh, wow..."

324
00:11:22,916 --> 00:11:24,666
[SAIKI] Great, I'm drawing
her attention.

325
00:11:24,750 --> 00:11:26,250
Don't want her
following me around,

326
00:11:26,333 --> 00:11:28,416
but don't wanna give in and say,
"Oh, wow!" either.

327
00:11:28,500 --> 00:11:30,708
Hm, I think I might
have a solution.

328
00:11:30,791 --> 00:11:32,166
[NENDOU]
Ah, we've arrived.

329
00:11:32,250 --> 00:11:33,333
There's the ramen shop.

330
00:11:33,416 --> 00:11:34,791
[SAIKI]
Stop making that face.

331
00:11:36,916 --> 00:11:38,291
Oh, wow.

332
00:11:38,375 --> 00:11:40,083
We're not going in there,
are we?

333
00:11:40,166 --> 00:11:41,875
[NENDOU] I hear their ramen's
crazy good!

334
00:11:41,958 --> 00:11:43,291
[TERUHASHI] No! No way!
I can't!

335
00:11:43,375 --> 00:11:44,875
My friend's cousin's
ex-dog-walker

336
00:11:44,958 --> 00:11:46,583
said it's good,
so it's gotta be good.

337
00:11:46,666 --> 00:11:48,541
[TERUHASHI] Is this like
an urban legend?

338
00:11:48,625 --> 00:11:51,083
I can't go in there!
This is me we're talking about!

339
00:11:51,166 --> 00:11:53,041
Of all the places they
could've brought me...

340
00:11:53,125 --> 00:11:56,125
[SAIKI] Just as I thought.
She'll split without going in.

341
00:11:56,208 --> 00:11:58,208
Something urgent just came up,
so I'm going home!

342
00:11:58,291 --> 00:11:59,958
[NENDOU] What?
[SAIKI] Because of that

343
00:12:00,041 --> 00:12:02,625
she'll be less likable.
They'll stop saying, "Oh, wow!"

344
00:12:02,708 --> 00:12:04,875
What's her problem?
She thinks she's too good.

345
00:12:04,958 --> 00:12:06,666
I guess she's not
like us common folk.

346
00:12:06,750 --> 00:12:08,166
[SAIKI]
Once her pride is wounded,

347
00:12:08,250 --> 00:12:09,791
Teruhashi will leave
me alone.

348
00:12:09,875 --> 00:12:12,041
[TERUHASHI] What's with them?
They're impossible!

349
00:12:12,125 --> 00:12:13,458
[SAIKI]
That's how it'll go.

350
00:12:13,541 --> 00:12:15,166
I'll tell 'em
something urgent came up.

351
00:12:15,250 --> 00:12:16,750
Something urgent
just came up, so--

352
00:12:16,833 --> 00:12:18,500
Are you out of your mind?
She's got class.

353
00:12:18,583 --> 00:12:20,333
No way she's gonna
eat at a place like that!

354
00:12:20,416 --> 00:12:22,833
You don't really wanna eat in
this rundown rat hole, do you?

355
00:12:22,916 --> 00:12:25,291
I'm okay with this place.

356
00:12:25,375 --> 00:12:26,583
I can't go home now.

357
00:12:26,666 --> 00:12:28,083
They'll think I'm stuck-up.

358
00:12:28,166 --> 00:12:30,875
[SAIKI] Kaidou, why'd you
have to push her?

359
00:12:30,958 --> 00:12:33,833
Her commitment to playing
the perfect woman is impressive.

360
00:12:34,958 --> 00:12:37,083
♪

361
00:12:37,166 --> 00:12:40,583
[TERUHASHI] Ha, there's no way
the inside could be clean.

362
00:12:40,666 --> 00:12:41,833
What was I thinking?

363
00:12:41,916 --> 00:12:43,875
What is this place?
It's filthy!

364
00:12:43,958 --> 00:12:46,458
Hey, seriously,
don't feel pressured to stay.

365
00:12:46,541 --> 00:12:48,416
I'm fine.
Taste is what matters.

366
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:50,833
[KAIDOU] She's so cool.
She doesn't look disappointed.

367
00:12:50,916 --> 00:12:52,833
She's perfect!
[TERUHASHI] "She's perfect!"

368
00:12:52,916 --> 00:12:55,083
You're totally right.
I've spent 16 years

369
00:12:55,166 --> 00:12:56,750
carefully crafting
the image of a girl

370
00:12:56,833 --> 00:12:58,625
with perfect appearance
and personality.

371
00:12:58,708 --> 00:13:00,833
I can't burst that bubble
in front of him!

372
00:13:00,916 --> 00:13:02,708
Besides I have
to keep alive the dream

373
00:13:02,791 --> 00:13:04,333
of all 7 billion people
on Earth.

374
00:13:04,416 --> 00:13:06,583
Yo, mister Manager!
Four ramen, please!

375
00:13:06,666 --> 00:13:07,708
Four ramen comin' up.

376
00:13:07,791 --> 00:13:09,750
[TERUHASHI] Oh wow.

377
00:13:09,833 --> 00:13:11,416
That slob is
the manager here?

378
00:13:11,500 --> 00:13:13,875
That monster who possesses every
trait I find repulsive?

379
00:13:13,958 --> 00:13:16,041
Is he gonna prepare our food?
No, it can't be!

380
00:13:16,125 --> 00:13:18,625
He's just giving our order
to the first-class chef!

381
00:13:18,708 --> 00:13:20,666
[SAIKI] Quit dreaming.
[MANAGER] Here you go.

382
00:13:20,750 --> 00:13:22,041
Ah, noodle time!

383
00:13:22,125 --> 00:13:23,333
[bubbles]

384
00:13:23,416 --> 00:13:25,333
[in unison] Oh, wow.

385
00:13:25,416 --> 00:13:27,875
[SAIKI] What you'd expect
from the shop's appearance.

386
00:13:27,958 --> 00:13:29,833
There goes my plan
to tank her likability.

387
00:13:29,916 --> 00:13:31,750
She can't eat this.
No one can.

388
00:13:31,833 --> 00:13:33,791
[TERUHASHI]
I have to eat it!

389
00:13:33,875 --> 00:13:36,083
They won't call me the perfect
woman if I leave the food

390
00:13:36,166 --> 00:13:37,625
that's been served to me
untouched!

391
00:13:37,708 --> 00:13:40,291
And I can't disillusion
7 billion people!

392
00:13:40,375 --> 00:13:41,500
[gasps]

393
00:13:41,583 --> 00:13:43,125
I don't think you
should eat that.

394
00:13:43,208 --> 00:13:46,000
[NENDOU] Hey, pops! Even pigs
wouldn't eat this slop!

395
00:13:46,083 --> 00:13:48,000
[KAIDOU] Teruhashi eats
stuff like this?

396
00:13:48,083 --> 00:13:49,750
[SAIKI]
The perfect woman, huh?

397
00:13:49,833 --> 00:13:52,416
Hm, if she'll go that far

398
00:13:52,500 --> 00:13:53,750
just to play
the perfect woman,

399
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:55,541
then maybe she actually
is perfect.

400
00:13:55,625 --> 00:13:56,958
[TERUHASHI]
I feel sick.

401
00:13:57,041 --> 00:13:59,833
♪

402
00:14:02,041 --> 00:14:03,958
[TORITSUKA]
My name is Reita Toritsuka,

403
00:14:04,041 --> 00:14:05,208
and I'm a psychic medium.

404
00:14:05,291 --> 00:14:06,458
From the time I was born,

405
00:14:06,541 --> 00:14:08,000
I've been able
to see ghosts.

406
00:14:08,083 --> 00:14:10,958
People think ghosts are scary,
but they're not.

407
00:14:11,041 --> 00:14:12,333
[GHOST] Hey.

408
00:14:12,416 --> 00:14:13,916
[TORITSUKA]
They're actually nice.

409
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,875
Have a good day
and watch out for cars.

410
00:14:15,958 --> 00:14:17,041
[TORITSUKA]
And helpful.

411
00:14:17,125 --> 00:14:18,708
Thanks! See?

412
00:14:18,791 --> 00:14:20,166
Ghosts are
completely harmless.

413
00:14:20,250 --> 00:14:21,833
I guess what I'm trying
to say is,

414
00:14:21,916 --> 00:14:23,541
the powers of a medium
are pretty great,

415
00:14:23,625 --> 00:14:24,958
and if you
play your cards right,

416
00:14:25,041 --> 00:14:26,458
they can lead
to world domination!

417
00:14:26,541 --> 00:14:27,875
Hey, you there!

418
00:14:27,958 --> 00:14:29,791
Are they searching bags
at the school today?

419
00:14:29,875 --> 00:14:31,458
You mean PK Academy?
In fact, they are!

420
00:14:31,541 --> 00:14:33,041
[TORITSUKA]
Knowledge is power.

421
00:14:33,125 --> 00:14:34,416
With ghosts as my
eyes and ears,

422
00:14:34,500 --> 00:14:36,708
there's no information
beyond my reach!

423
00:14:36,791 --> 00:14:39,666
And he who controls the
information, controls the world!

424
00:14:39,750 --> 00:14:41,958
[GHOST] What kind of filth are
you bringing to school?

425
00:14:42,041 --> 00:14:43,666
[TORITSUKA]
I'm using my natural gifts

426
00:14:43,750 --> 00:14:45,916
to get ahead in life and achieve
a little happiness.

427
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:49,041
It's no different than what
rock stars and athletes do.

428
00:14:49,125 --> 00:14:51,166
Hey, can I ask you
to do one more favor for me?

429
00:14:51,250 --> 00:14:52,166
Sure, you name it.

430
00:14:52,250 --> 00:14:54,083
There! Tell me what color

431
00:14:54,166 --> 00:14:55,375
her panties are!

432
00:14:55,458 --> 00:14:56,791
I can't do that.

433
00:14:56,875 --> 00:14:58,666
It's an invasion of privacy.
And creepy.

434
00:14:58,750 --> 00:15:00,166
Well, see you around.

435
00:15:00,250 --> 00:15:02,375
[TORITSUKA] Like I said,
ghosts are really nice.

436
00:15:02,458 --> 00:15:04,958
So of course, they refuse
to take part in dirty deeds.

437
00:15:05,041 --> 00:15:06,416
[bell ringing]

438
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:08,083
[TORITSUKA] In any case,
the benefits

439
00:15:08,166 --> 00:15:09,666
of being a medium
don't stop there!

440
00:15:09,750 --> 00:15:10,916
[ARIYOSHI] I'm at a loss.

441
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:12,375
Hello, ladies!
I've got some time

442
00:15:12,458 --> 00:15:14,250
if you wanna hear about
guardian spirits!

443
00:15:14,333 --> 00:15:16,666
Chicks are totally
into this spiritual crap.

444
00:15:16,750 --> 00:15:19,375
Huh, maybe I should start
a business with these powers.

445
00:15:19,458 --> 00:15:20,916
I could make a fortune!

446
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:23,041
This is a ceremony
to exorcise evil spirits.

447
00:15:23,125 --> 00:15:25,333
For your own safety,
please remove all your clothing.

448
00:15:25,416 --> 00:15:26,791
[GIRL]
Whatever you say.

449
00:15:26,875 --> 00:15:28,708
He's already told me
everything about mine.

450
00:15:28,791 --> 00:15:30,125
Oh, you should
have him do yours.

451
00:15:30,208 --> 00:15:31,875
[KANAZAWA] I'm not into
spiritual crap.

452
00:15:31,958 --> 00:15:34,125
Forget spirits. There's
something we wanna ask you.

453
00:15:34,208 --> 00:15:36,333
Her gym clothes went missing.
Do you know anything?

454
00:15:36,416 --> 00:15:38,666
No, no! I don't know anything!
It wasn't me! I swear...!

455
00:15:38,750 --> 00:15:41,041
[YABE] I was just asking
if you'd seen 'em.

456
00:15:41,125 --> 00:15:43,500
That's it! I'll find
those gym clothes for you!

457
00:15:43,583 --> 00:15:44,916
[in unison] What?

458
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:46,708
I don't get it.
How, guardian spirits guy?

459
00:15:46,791 --> 00:15:48,125
Yeah, how?
Do you have any leads,

460
00:15:48,208 --> 00:15:49,416
With guardian spirits?

461
00:15:49,500 --> 00:15:51,041
Well, first,
the name's Toritsuka.

462
00:15:51,125 --> 00:15:52,333
And I do have leads.

463
00:15:52,416 --> 00:15:54,000
There are ghosts
all over this school.

464
00:15:54,083 --> 00:15:56,125
They know everything
that happens. I can ask them.

465
00:15:57,708 --> 00:15:59,750
[TORITSUKA] Hey, ghost.
Let me ask you.

466
00:15:59,833 --> 00:16:01,500
I'm looking
for this girl's gym clothes.

467
00:16:01,583 --> 00:16:03,041
You know where I might
find 'em?

468
00:16:03,125 --> 00:16:04,625
Huh? What kind
of sick stuff

469
00:16:04,708 --> 00:16:06,916
you gonna do with those clothes
when you get 'em, perv?

470
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:09,041
[TORITSUKA] You got
the wrong idea! She asked me!

471
00:16:09,125 --> 00:16:11,416
Oh, whoops, sorry about that.
Then yeah, I saw 'em.

472
00:16:11,500 --> 00:16:13,041
When and where?
Not long ago.

473
00:16:13,125 --> 00:16:14,875
Think it was when I was
goofing off,

474
00:16:14,958 --> 00:16:16,541
floating inside
your Vice Principal.

475
00:16:16,625 --> 00:16:18,625
[TORITSUKA] Is that fun?
[GHOST] Eh, not really.

476
00:16:18,708 --> 00:16:20,125
Anyway, I saw a boy walk by

477
00:16:20,208 --> 00:16:21,708
carrying a girl's gym bag.

478
00:16:21,791 --> 00:16:22,958
Seemed odd at the time.

479
00:16:23,041 --> 00:16:24,625
[TORITSUKA]
The clothes were stolen?

480
00:16:24,708 --> 00:16:27,625
This story just got a whole lot
more exciting!

481
00:16:27,708 --> 00:16:30,500
When word spreads that I solved
a robbery, I'll be a hero!

482
00:16:30,583 --> 00:16:32,416
[GIRL 1] I heard he
caught a thief by himself!

483
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:34,333
[GIRL 2] That's amazing!
I hope he's single!

484
00:16:34,416 --> 00:16:35,833
[GIRL 3] All that,
and so handsome!

485
00:16:35,916 --> 00:16:39,041
[TORITSUKA] Ha, my dream
knows no bounds!

486
00:16:39,125 --> 00:16:40,708
That's him!
[GHOST] Stop right there!

487
00:16:40,791 --> 00:16:42,333
You're the guy
from this morning--

488
00:16:42,416 --> 00:16:44,666
I'm that troubled boy's
guardian spirit! Leave him be!

489
00:16:44,750 --> 00:16:46,958
So you're okay aiding in his
dirty deeds, but not mine?

490
00:16:47,041 --> 00:16:48,666
I beg you!
[TORITSUKA] You really gonna

491
00:16:48,750 --> 00:16:50,458
stand in my way?
[GHOST] As his guardian--

492
00:16:50,541 --> 00:16:52,208
[TORITSUKA] Okay.
[GHOST] No, stop!

493
00:16:52,291 --> 00:16:54,625
I'll do anything you want,
please, just leave him alone!

494
00:16:54,708 --> 00:16:56,208
Anything?
[GHOST] That's right!

495
00:16:56,291 --> 00:16:58,416
I can tell you people's
weaknesses, help you cheat,

496
00:16:58,500 --> 00:17:00,750
get you whatever information
you desire!

497
00:17:00,833 --> 00:17:02,458
All you have to do
is look the other way!

498
00:17:02,541 --> 00:17:04,208
Thanks, but no thanks.

499
00:17:04,291 --> 00:17:05,333
[gasps] Really, why?

500
00:17:05,416 --> 00:17:06,666
[TORITSUKA]
I was tempted.

501
00:17:06,750 --> 00:17:08,291
But there's this super
scary psychic

502
00:17:08,375 --> 00:17:09,500
roaming the halls.

503
00:17:09,583 --> 00:17:10,833
He's kind of
a goody two-shoes.

504
00:17:10,916 --> 00:17:12,250
He sees everything
that goes on,

505
00:17:12,333 --> 00:17:13,458
even in people's heads.

506
00:17:13,541 --> 00:17:15,333
If he found out
I let a creep

507
00:17:15,416 --> 00:17:17,625
get away with that just so I
could do bad things myself,

508
00:17:17,708 --> 00:17:19,291
he'd blow me up
with his mind.

509
00:17:19,375 --> 00:17:20,875
I know you're
doing whatever it takes

510
00:17:20,958 --> 00:17:22,333
to protect the kid
you watch over,

511
00:17:22,416 --> 00:17:24,125
so I'd feel guilty
taking advantage of you

512
00:17:24,208 --> 00:17:25,833
and making you
compromise your values.

513
00:17:25,916 --> 00:17:27,458
Plus, I really
wanna be a hero!

514
00:17:27,541 --> 00:17:29,541
Come out, you perv!
[GHOST] Wait! He's a good kid!

515
00:17:29,625 --> 00:17:32,750
Huh? He's not here.
But that girl's gym clothes are.

516
00:17:32,833 --> 00:17:34,500
He probably jumped out
that window there

517
00:17:34,583 --> 00:17:36,083
when he heard you coming.
[GIRLS] Ah!

518
00:17:36,166 --> 00:17:37,458
Those are
Ariyoshi's clothes!

519
00:17:37,541 --> 00:17:38,916
It was you who took
them all along!

520
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:40,208
We thought
it was suspicious,

521
00:17:40,291 --> 00:17:41,750
you freaking out
earlier, you perv!

522
00:17:41,833 --> 00:17:43,916
No, wait!
You've got it wrong!

523
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:46,583
Sorry, I really appreciate
you taking the blame for him.

524
00:17:46,666 --> 00:17:48,791
[TORITSUKA] What was I
thinking? My powers suck.

525
00:17:48,875 --> 00:17:50,125
Being a medium is the worst!

526
00:17:50,208 --> 00:17:51,541
Aw, cheer up.
Just this once,

527
00:17:51,625 --> 00:17:53,250
I made a point to check
the color of those

528
00:17:53,333 --> 00:17:54,541
poor girls' panties
for you.

529
00:17:54,625 --> 00:17:57,041
That's probably small
comfort to you.

530
00:17:57,125 --> 00:17:59,541
[TORITSUKA] Being a medium
is awesome!

531
00:17:59,625 --> 00:18:02,000
[SAIKI] Why wasn't I
in this episode?

532
00:18:02,083 --> 00:18:06,375
[man singing in Japanese]

533
00:18:07,625 --> 00:18:11,041
♪

534
00:18:12,833 --> 00:18:14,833
[SAIKI] Within 0.2 seconds
of waking up,

535
00:18:14,916 --> 00:18:17,500
I realized that my
supernatural powers were gone.

536
00:18:17,583 --> 00:18:19,375
First off,
I don't hear voices.

537
00:18:19,458 --> 00:18:20,916
Normally,
as soon as I wake up,

538
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:22,916
people's thoughts
come flooding into my head,

539
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:25,291
making me wish I could sleep
through the rest of my life.

540
00:18:25,375 --> 00:18:26,958
I can't float
in the air either.

541
00:18:28,208 --> 00:18:29,333
[SAIKI] Ow.

542
00:18:29,416 --> 00:18:30,916
My punch didn't
even make a crack.

543
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:32,708
Usually, it would
obliterate the wall

544
00:18:32,791 --> 00:18:35,208
and everything else seven
kilometers in that direction.

545
00:18:35,291 --> 00:18:37,833
I've been freed from the curse
that is my psychic powers!

546
00:18:37,916 --> 00:18:39,541
Finally! I'm free--

547
00:18:39,625 --> 00:18:41,208
Uh...

548
00:18:41,291 --> 00:18:44,750
And 0.2 seconds later,
I realized it was all a dream.

549
00:18:44,833 --> 00:18:47,833
[MAN] Morning already? Well,
another day closer to death.

550
00:18:47,916 --> 00:18:49,875
♪

551
00:18:49,958 --> 00:18:51,166
[SAIKI]
Well, of course.

552
00:18:51,250 --> 00:18:53,291
Nah, I probably shouldn't.

553
00:18:53,375 --> 00:18:56,041
What a disappointment.
This morning is the worst.

554
00:18:56,125 --> 00:18:59,625
Plus, I had that dream and now
I've got a killer headache.

555
00:18:59,708 --> 00:19:01,666
Whenever I have a dream,
followed by a headache,

556
00:19:01,750 --> 00:19:03,333
my precognition powers
kick in.

557
00:19:03,416 --> 00:19:05,333
They allow me to see
what happens in the future.

558
00:19:05,416 --> 00:19:06,833
And by "allow,"
I mean "force."

559
00:19:06,916 --> 00:19:08,875
Unfortunately,
that dream wasn't foretelling

560
00:19:08,958 --> 00:19:10,083
that I would
lose my powers.

561
00:19:10,166 --> 00:19:11,833
No, it foretold
the explosion.

562
00:19:11,916 --> 00:19:15,708
Fine. I guess I'll have to save
some lives before breakfast.

563
00:19:17,500 --> 00:19:19,583
This must be the place
that blew up in my dream.

564
00:19:19,666 --> 00:19:21,500
My house is right around
the corner.

565
00:19:21,583 --> 00:19:23,791
I only take action when
things are gonna personally

566
00:19:23,875 --> 00:19:25,541
cause me harm
or inconvenience.

567
00:19:25,625 --> 00:19:28,583
If my actions happen to also
save other people, so be it.

568
00:19:28,666 --> 00:19:30,583
But generally speaking,
that's never my goal.

569
00:19:30,666 --> 00:19:33,666
I've saved the world
and mankind six times so far,

570
00:19:33,750 --> 00:19:36,083
though only because my own
existence was threatened.

571
00:19:36,166 --> 00:19:37,458
But back to this explosion.

572
00:19:38,833 --> 00:19:40,958
Well, there you go.
Crisis averted.

573
00:19:41,041 --> 00:19:43,166
You may think I'm kidding,
but I'm not.

574
00:19:43,250 --> 00:19:44,875
An accident usually happens
as a result

575
00:19:44,958 --> 00:19:46,708
of a specific
series of events.

576
00:19:46,791 --> 00:19:49,541
So one tiny change can lead to
an entirely different outcome.

577
00:19:49,625 --> 00:19:52,000
Let's look into the future where
I didn't change the rock.

578
00:19:52,083 --> 00:19:54,500
One minute from now, a high-
school girl will run this way.

579
00:19:54,583 --> 00:19:57,166
She's wearing a miniskirt even
though it's the dead of winter.

580
00:19:57,250 --> 00:20:00,000
She'll slip on the rock and
tumble violently into the air,

581
00:20:00,083 --> 00:20:01,833
almost like she's doing
a somersault kick.

582
00:20:01,916 --> 00:20:03,541
This maneuver will send
the rock flying

583
00:20:03,625 --> 00:20:05,125
straight towards
an oil tanker.

584
00:20:05,208 --> 00:20:07,166
At that moment, the driver
will lower the window

585
00:20:07,250 --> 00:20:08,750
to talk to the gas station
attendant,

586
00:20:08,833 --> 00:20:10,250
and the rock'll hit
him in the head.

587
00:20:10,333 --> 00:20:11,791
He'll fall forward
as he passes out,

588
00:20:11,875 --> 00:20:13,541
His foot'll press
the gas pedal.

589
00:20:13,625 --> 00:20:16,041
The tanker will move forward,
crashing into a gas pump.

590
00:20:16,125 --> 00:20:17,875
Gasoline will
leak everywhere.

591
00:20:17,958 --> 00:20:19,333
Meanwhile,
the girl who slipped

592
00:20:19,416 --> 00:20:21,375
will have landed
in a less-than-ladylike pose.

593
00:20:21,458 --> 00:20:22,958
That hurt.
[SAIKI] Just then,

594
00:20:23,041 --> 00:20:24,541
a man on a scooter
will pass by,

595
00:20:24,625 --> 00:20:26,416
his attention diverted.
[MAN] Ha, ha.

596
00:20:26,500 --> 00:20:28,958
[SAIKI] As a result, he'll wipe
out on the spilled gas.

597
00:20:29,041 --> 00:20:30,916
The scooter will slide
into the gas station,

598
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:33,333
which'll lead
to a big explosion.

599
00:20:33,416 --> 00:20:34,833
So that's what
would've happened.

600
00:20:34,916 --> 00:20:36,125
You get it now?

601
00:20:36,208 --> 00:20:37,541
The accident
was gonna be caused

602
00:20:37,625 --> 00:20:39,291
by a series of unlikely
coincidences,

603
00:20:39,375 --> 00:20:40,875
like the kind
you see in manga.

604
00:20:40,958 --> 00:20:42,416
If the schoolgirl
wasn't running,

605
00:20:42,500 --> 00:20:44,333
then she wouldn't have
tripped on that rock,

606
00:20:44,416 --> 00:20:45,708
landing bottoms up.

607
00:20:45,791 --> 00:20:47,500
If she'd worn sweatpants
under her skirt,

608
00:20:47,583 --> 00:20:49,541
the perv on the scooter
wouldn't have wiped out.

609
00:20:49,625 --> 00:20:50,750
[MAN]
Nothin' to see here.

610
00:20:50,833 --> 00:20:52,291
[SAIKI]
There's the truck driver,

611
00:20:52,375 --> 00:20:54,458
who, if he'd rolled down
his window a second later,

612
00:20:54,541 --> 00:20:55,958
wouldn't have been hit
by the rock.

613
00:20:56,041 --> 00:20:57,541
Or if he'd had
even a modicum of skill,

614
00:20:57,625 --> 00:20:59,208
he could've caught it.
[MAN] Nice try.

615
00:20:59,291 --> 00:21:00,958
[SAIKI] No matter how big
an accident is,

616
00:21:01,041 --> 00:21:02,791
it's always triggered
by something minor,

617
00:21:02,875 --> 00:21:04,875
and so a minor change
is all it takes to prevent it.

618
00:21:04,958 --> 00:21:06,291
It was easy this time,

619
00:21:06,375 --> 00:21:07,958
since I saw the whole thing
in my dream.

620
00:21:08,041 --> 00:21:09,541
But normally,
I only see a part of it,

621
00:21:09,625 --> 00:21:11,375
which can make my job
much harder.

622
00:21:11,458 --> 00:21:13,750
[grunts]

623
00:21:13,833 --> 00:21:16,166
I had another
premonition just then.

624
00:21:16,250 --> 00:21:18,541
And this time, all I saw
was the end result.

625
00:21:18,625 --> 00:21:20,166
Seriously?
[NENDOU] Ouchy!

626
00:21:20,250 --> 00:21:22,416
Where'd this rock come from
all of a sudden?

627
00:21:22,500 --> 00:21:24,416
Huh? Could it be?

628
00:21:24,500 --> 00:21:26,791
Yes! It's definitely a meteor
from outer space!

629
00:21:26,875 --> 00:21:28,500
♪

630
00:21:28,583 --> 00:21:30,833
[HAIRO] Sir! I brought all
the kerosene for the heaters

631
00:21:30,916 --> 00:21:32,583
in from the shed!
[TEACHER] Oh, thank y--

632
00:21:32,666 --> 00:21:34,583
We don't need all that!
We're not trying to turn

633
00:21:34,666 --> 00:21:36,083
the teachers' lounge
into a sauna!

634
00:21:36,166 --> 00:21:37,666
[HAIRO] Sorry!
Lemme take some back!

635
00:21:37,750 --> 00:21:39,250
[TEACHER] That's not necessary.

636
00:21:39,333 --> 00:21:41,208
Leave 'em in the hallway.
I'll take care of it.

637
00:21:41,291 --> 00:21:43,208
[HAIRO] You got it!
[NENDOU] Hey! Check it out!

638
00:21:43,291 --> 00:21:45,541
Ya ever seen a meteor before?
Isn't it amazing?

639
00:21:45,625 --> 00:21:46,958
It's from outer space,
you know?

640
00:21:47,041 --> 00:21:48,166
It's not a meteor, stupid,

641
00:21:48,250 --> 00:21:49,416
it's just a plain, old rock.

642
00:21:49,500 --> 00:21:50,875
[NENDOU]
Hey! What're you doing?

643
00:21:50,958 --> 00:21:52,958
You mighta hit someone!
[KAIDOU] There's no one.

644
00:21:53,041 --> 00:21:55,666
[TAKAHASHI] I overslept! I've
got class assistant duty today!

645
00:21:55,750 --> 00:21:57,458
I've gotta book it
if I'm gonna make it!

646
00:21:57,541 --> 00:21:59,916
I know they say never to run
'cause we might trip and fall,

647
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:01,333
but I have no choi--
And I tripped!

648
00:22:08,125 --> 00:22:10,208
[SAIKI] See? It's always
something minor

649
00:22:10,291 --> 00:22:11,958
that triggers an accident.

650
00:22:12,041 --> 00:22:13,958
♪

651
00:22:21,666 --> 00:22:24,541
[woman singing in Japanese]

652
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:43,833
[SAIKI]
Seriously, I could talk about

653
00:23:43,916 --> 00:23:45,291
how good coffee
jelly is for days.

654
00:23:45,375 --> 00:23:46,750
It's just so good.

655
00:23:46,833 --> 00:23:48,791
Whoops, I let myself
indulge in happiness.

656
00:23:48,875 --> 00:23:50,500
How unlike me.
Next time on

657
00:23:50,583 --> 00:23:52,125
<i>The Disastrous Life</i>
<i>of Saiki K,</i>

658
00:23:52,208 --> 00:23:54,458
if you ask me if I'm
a cat person or a dog person,

659
00:23:54,541 --> 00:23:56,833
the answer is,
"I don't care."

